episodes.title: Give Peace a Chance
episodes.plot: The boys return from a stint in jail to discover that Cory and Trevor have squandered all of the pot profits; Lahey's time in a mental institution seems to have done him some good.

episodes.title: The Shit Puppets
episodes.plot: Julian takes Cory and Trevor to work as a way for them to pay back the pot-harvest money they blew. The boys are surprised to discover that the work involves using guns.

episodes.title: The Fuckin' Way She Goes
episodes.plot: Julian, Ricky, and the boys hide 100 kilos of hash in plain sight. Something unexpected gets burned up due to a celebratory barbecue.

episodes.title: You Got to Blame the Thing Up Here
episodes.plot: Bubbles takes the blame for something Ricky did. Julian uses gumball machines to finance a money-making scheme.

episodes.title: Mr. Lahey Is a Fuckin' Drunk, and He Always Will Be
episodes.plot: Ricky's feeling a tiny bit bad about the fire he caused. Randy's worried because Lahey is constantly talking about not drinking.

episodes.title: Don't Cross the Shitline
episodes.plot: J-Roc's porn filming leads to unexpected complications.

episodes.title: The Winds of Shit
episodes.plot: Lahey thinks up a plan that will put Julian back in jail.

episodes.title: Dressed All Over & Zesty Mordant
episodes.plot: The boys prepare to ship hash in shopping carts, under Lahey's secret surveillance.

episodes.title: I Am the Liquor
episodes.plot: Julian makes payments towards his trailer; he wants it back before bailing Ray out of jail. Ricky isn't happy about this when he finds out. Lahey bails out Cyrus, Dennis and Terry so that they will seek to get their hash back from the Boys.

episodes.title: The Shit Blizzard
episodes.plot: Cyrus, Dennis, and Terry get released from jail and return to Sunnyvale to try to get their hash from the boys.
